								<div class="col-lg-12 text-justify">
									<p>We started the event at 8:30 in the morning with a
										registration of guests and participants, followed by the
										opening prayer and singing of the National Anthem. Dr. Annabee
										Magbanua-Claur (Dean College of Arts and Sciences) gave the
										opening remarks. Then, Dr. Reymund Sabay (Project Director,
										ROLEx) gave his speech. He gave a preview of Project Rolex,
										explaining what Rolex is all about while presenting some
										slides to all the participants. After that ROLEx Introduction,
										Dr. Ma. Corazon G. Acaba, DVM (Project Proponent, ROLEx)
										introduce the resource speaker, Mr. Oscar Bulaong Jr., PhD.</p>
									<p>Mr. Bulaong told a brief history about himself, what he
										has gone through. He then ask the participants if where they
										came from and discussed how the flow of the activities will
										be. He also started the lecture by asking the question "How
										can we do ethics formation?", then he began to discuss how we
										can do ethics formation. Along the discussion, He present a
										book entitled "Alone Together" and he told a story about
										"Three Stonemasons". Some of the participants gave their
										reaction about the story of "Three Stonemasons" and added
										something about it. The speaker also present a video of Richie
										Fernando - a Jesuit Brother who died in Cambodia shielding his
										students from a grenade explosion will soon be on the path of
										sainthood. After that, he discussed the Four Pillars of
										Learning. Then he held a group activity which is a Micro Case
										Writing. He also show an example of case study entitled "A
										Harmless Raffle Prize", this study is about bribery.
										Participants gave their reflection about the said study. The
										morning session ended with another group activity - a Micro
										Case Analysis.</p>
									<p>In afternoon, Mr. Bulaong started the session with a
										presentation and discussion of Case Analysis. Each group had
										their representative to explain their work in front of
										everyone. Each representative won a prize which is an organic
										bitter gourd (Ampalaya). The speaker gave his reaction after
										each group presented their work. After the presentation, he
										ask everyone in the room to stand-up and follow him while
										doing some stretching to awaken their mind and body. Then, he
										started another discussion about Ethical Leadership that
										explain why it is important. A leadership that is leading by
										respect for ethical beliefs and values and Comparing Technical
										Problem and Adaptive Challenge. After the discussion another
										group activity takes place and after that, they presented
										their work.</p>
									<p>After the group presentation, Mr. Bulaong gave his
										reaction and close the program with a quote "Success has many
										fathers, failure is an orphan". After the program, a mass held
										in one of the chapel inside the UNO-Recoletos Campus.</p>
